OL,6,FMr Kretinsky is believed to have made
OL,7,Fseveral other concessions to gain
OL,8,Fapproval, including allowing workers
OL,9,Fto get a 10% share of any dividends
OL,10,Fpaid out to him and giving the
OL,11,FGovernment a "golden share" in the
OL,12,Fpostal service.
OL,14,FHe also committed not to raid the
OL,15,Fpensions surplus, to maintain the
OL,16,Funiversal service and the brand name,
OL,17,Fplus to keep tax residency in the UK
OL,18,Ffor five years.
